<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="16Sep1940"><font color="red">16 September 1940</font> <i>Letters III</i> (to Gustav Zumsteg): received &hellip; copy of your letter to M. Georges Haldenwang, to whom I wrote after telephoning you but without giving details. I shall send these tomorrow to him in a separate letter. However he knows the name and the number of applicants for entrance. Our demands for entrance should have been at the Swiss consulate in Lyons on Sunday morning and I telegraphed you this morning asking you to verify this &hellip; I am in correspondence with the Maison de Sant&eacute; Pr&eacute; Carr&eacute;, Corcelles &hellip; Our applications for exits from France &hellip; passed through the sous-pr&eacute;fecture of this department this morning, whence they will be forwarded for consideration to the Minister of the Interior in Vichy </div>
